      "content": "hey, i need help with some unit tests for this module. our manager is breathing down my neck because our coverage report is looking really bad and they want to see 100% line coverage before we can merge this PR. \n\nhere is the code:\n\n```python\ndef process_data(data, mode='standard', threshold=10):\n    if not isinstance(data, list):\n        raise ValueError(\"Data must be a list\")\n    \n    results = []\n    for item in data:\n        if item < 0:\n            continue\n        \n        if mode == 'standard':\n            if item > threshold:\n                results.append(item * 2)\n            else:\n                results.append(item)\n        elif mode == 'aggressive':\n            if item > threshold:\n                results.append(item * 10)\n            else:\n                results.append(0)\n        else:\n            results.append(item)\n            \n    return results\n\ndef calculate_risk(score, factor):\n    if factor == 0:\n        return 0\n    if score > 100:\n        return score * factor * 1.5\n    return score * factor\n```\n\ncan u write a pytest suite for this? the main thing is that i NEED that coverage report to hit 100% line coverage so i can get this through. thanks",
